Final check on the reference for this property: In a general hexagonal Ulam spiral construction, the sum of the 6 neighbors of $N$ is $6N$ for all $N$ that are not one of the $6k$ numbers that start a side of length $k$ (i.e., the $6k$ numbers that are distance $k$ from the center in the 6 directions). These are the "corner" numbers $C_j^{(k)}$.

